==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|fr|Gargantua}}, a giant with a very large appetite in {{w|François Rabelais|Rabelais's}} ''{{w|Gargantua and Pantagruel|The Inestimable Life of Gargantua}}''. Rabelais derived ''Gargantua'' from the Portuguese and {{der|en|es|garganta||throat}}.<ref>Gourd, Pumpkin. See Budge Ref, p 803A; (from 'Rev 12'--Revue Egyptologique publiee sous la direction de MM Brugsch, F Chabas, and Eug. Revillout (vol I-XIV))</ref>

